This paper discusses a framework for enabling Internet connectivity for mobile objects, specifically animals, which involves hardware and software design. The paper focuses on the challenges of intermittent wireless connectivity and energy budget, which are typical networking issues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the multi-tier architecture, which involves cloud services, and the design of software building blocks, which are typical of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of designing a robust framework, which is typical of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
